        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(webvnc): force VNC password authentication",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add `webvnc local --security-type auto|vnc`\n- force standard VNC password authentication for macOS launchers while preserving the existing default\n- cover RFB negotiation, cancellation, and flag validation\n\n## Why\n\nmacOS Screen Sharing can advertise Apple Remote Desktop authentication before standard VNC password authentication. noVNC follows that order, so browser connections can fail even when legacy VNC authentication is enabled. The bridge now filters only the initial RFB security offer when explicitly requested and leaves the rest of the stream untouched.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `go test ./internal/cli -run 'Test(ForceRFBVNCAuthentication|MacOSWebVNC|WebVNCLocal|ServeLocalWebVNCBridge|ReadLocalWebVNCPassword|ReserveLocalWebVNCBrowserPort)' -count=1`\n- `go vet ./internal/cli`\n- docs build\n",
